  "prompt": "What steps can be taken to make Delhi a pollution-free city?",
  "response": "Here are several steps to help reduce pollution in Delhi:\n\n1. Transportation Sector\n- Promote electric vehicles\n- Improve public transportation\n- Encourage cycling and walking\n- Implement stricter vehicle emission standards\n- Develop better metro and bus networks\n\n2. Industrial Pollution Control\n- Enforce stringent emission regulations\n- Mandate pollution control equipment\n- Shift to cleaner technologies\n- Regular industrial emissions monitoring\n- Penalize non-compliant industries\n\n3. Construction and Waste Management\n- Implement dust control measures\n- Proper waste segregation\n- Promote recycling\n- Ban open waste burning\n- Use construction site dust barriers\n\n4. Agricultural Practices\n- Discourage crop burning\n- Provide alternatives for crop residue management\n- Subsidize modern agricultural equipment\n- Educate farmers about environmental impact\n\n5. Green Initiatives\n- Increase urban green cover\n- Plant more trees\n- Develop urban forests\n- Create green corridors\n- Encourage rooftop gardens\n\n6. Policy and Regulatory Measures\n- Strengthen environmental laws\n- Impose strict penalties for pollution\n- Develop comprehensive air quality management plans\n- Promote public awareness\n- Incentivize green practices\n\n7. Technology and Monitoring\n- Install advanced air quality monitoring systems\n- Use real-time pollution tracking\n- Develop early warning mechanisms",
